1.title: Gio
1.plot: An outgoing entertainer, who numbs his negative emotions with junk food, fights to get control of his health so that he can live life to the fullest.

2.title: Christine
2.plot: A 54-year-old mom and grandmother realizes that after decades of excuses, she needs to regain control over her health and fitness or risk developing a life-threatening disease.

3.title: Carla
3.plot: A young woman, whose life was changed forever after a spinal cord injury, wants to get back to the healthy and happy person she once was. But is she ready to put in the hard work to make the change she so desperately needs?

4.title: Kristina
4.plot: A young woman, whose life was changed forever after a spinal cord injury, wants to get back to the healthy and happy person she once was. But is she ready to put in the hard work to make the change she so desperately needs?

5.title: Dawn
5.plot: A single mom working long hours in the ER knows the devastating effects of obesity and is terrified that if she doesn't get her weight under control, she won't be around to raise her son.

6.title: Archie
6.plot: This overweight 42-year-old father of two fears his poor habits will lead him to an early grave. Can he change his future by confronting the issues in his past?

7.title: Debbie
7.plot: A workaholic mother of two comes to realize that constantly being 'on the clock' is seriously compromising her health. Can she find a balance before it's too late?

8.title: Tony
8.plot: A former elite athlete who gained weight since getting a promotion and becoming a father, overhauls his busy lifestyle in hopes of rediscovering his healthy self.

imdb.plot outline: The new documentary series Mind Set Go follows the three-month wellness journey of eight Canadians as they discover the barriers preventing them from optimum health in mind, body, and soul. In each episode, one participant seeks to understand and overcome their negative coping behaviours, all with the encouragement and insight of various Canadian Paralympian and athlete experts who have triumphed over their own adversity and learned that a positive mindset is the key to overcoming barriers. At the end of three months, each participant tackles a physical objective that reveals how their lives and attitudes have progressed over the course of their journey to health.
